docs.abstract: The president can instruct executive branch agencies to shield key evidence if he chooses. But it is unlikely that he alone can shake off the dragnet stretched across Trump world by Democrats.
docs.snippet: The president can instruct executive branch agencies to shield key evidence if he chooses. But it is unlikely that he alone can shake off the dragnet stretched across Trump world by Democrats.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump dismissed on Tuesday an expansive document request by House Democrats scrutinizing whether he obstructed justice or abused power as nothing more than a political sideshow — and he suggested the White House might not cooperate.

headline.main: Trump Dismisses 81 House Document Requests. Here’s Where They Went.
headline.print_headline: Detailed Request for Documents That Digs Deep Into Trump’s World

docs.abstract: The WikiLeaks source refused to answer questions before a grand jury about her interactions with the group, whose leader, Julian Assange, has been charged.
docs.snippet: The WikiLeaks source refused to answer questions before a grand jury about her interactions with the group, whose leader, Julian Assange, has been charged.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Chelsea Manning, the former Army intelligence analyst who sent archives of secret military and diplomatic documents to WikiLeaks in 2010, said on Thursday that she had refused to answer questions about her interactions with the antisecrecy organization before a grand jury — and might be sent to jail as soon as Friday.

headline.main: Chelsea Manning Says She May Be Jailed for Contempt of Court
headline.print_headline: Manning May Be Jailed for Silence on Stand

docs.abstract: The former chief of staff says a complete border wall would be a “waste of money” and declines to answer questions about Jared Kushner’s security clearance.
docs.snippet: The former chief of staff says a complete border wall would be a “waste of money” and declines to answer questions about Jared Kushner’s security clearance.
docs.lead_paragraph: The former White House chief of staff, John F. Kelly, on Wednesday declined to answer questions about the existence of a memo he wrote saying that President Trump had ordered officials to give his son-in-law, Jared Kushner, a security clearance in May 2018.

headline.main: John Kelly, Out of White House, Breaks With Trump Policies
headline.print_headline: Kelly, Out of White House, Breaks With Policies of His Former Boss

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Senator Mitch McConnell, the majority leader, extended a bipartisan invitation on Monday to the head of NATO to address a joint session of Congress, in an unsubtle jab at President Trump’s foreign policy that is meant to underscore broad congressional support for the alliance.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On Friday, the White House announced that Karen Pence, the second lady, would lead a delegation to the United Arab Emirates in support of disabled American athletes at the Special Olympics. On Monday, the White House’s budget proposed striking $17.6 million in grants to expand the event.

headline.main: Trump Lauded Farmers, Medicare and AIDS Programs. Then Came His Budget Knife.
headline.print_headline: President’s Budget Plan Makes Deep Cuts to Programs He Brags About

docs.abstract: The House Judiciary Committee on Monday sent document requests to 81 agencies, individuals and entities tied to President Trump, beginning a broad obstruction and corruption inquiry.
docs.snippet: The House Judiciary Committee on Monday sent document requests to 81 agencies, individuals and entities tied to President Trump, beginning a broad obstruction and corruption inquiry.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The chairman of the House Judiciary Committee delivered a flurry of demands for documents from the executive branch and the broader Trump world on Monday that detailed the breadth and ambition of a new investigation into possible obstruction of justice, corruption and abuse of power by President Trump and his administration.

headline.main: With Sweeping Document Request, Democrats Launch Broad Trump Corruption Inquiry
headline.print_headline: Democrats Reveal Vast Scope of Trump Inquiry

docs.abstract: President Trump’s top trade negotiator told lawmakers that he could not predict success in ending the trade war, offering a more cautious assessment than other administration officials.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s top trade negotiator told lawmakers that he could not predict success in ending the trade war, offering a more cautious assessment than other administration officials.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s top trade negotiator raised doubts on Tuesday that a trade agreement with China was within reach, saying that “major issues” must still be resolved and that it was impossible at this point to predict success.

headline.main: Lighthizer Casts Doubts on China Trade Talks as ‘Major Issues’ Go Unresolved

docs.abstract: Doctors, hospitals, drug companies and insurers have a simple message: The Affordable Care Act works reasonably well and should be improved, not repealed or replaced with a big new public program.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Even before Democrats finish drafting bills to create a single-payer health care system, the health care and insurance industries have assembled a small army of lobbyists to kill “Medicare for all,” an idea that is mocked publicly but is being greeted privately with increasing seriousness.

headline.main: Health Care and Insurance Industries Mobilize to Kill ‘Medicare for All’
headline.print_headline: Eager to Sink Medicare Plan, Lobbies Unite

docs.abstract: Confirmation hearings for the Supreme Court nominee Brett M. Kavanaugh opened with protests and theater, as Democrats unleashed a fierce barrage.
docs.snippet: Confirmation hearings for the Supreme Court nominee Brett M. Kavanaugh opened with protests and theater, as Democrats unleashed a fierce barrage.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Democrats tore into President Trump’s Supreme Court nominee on Tuesday, painting Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh as a narrow-minded partisan as the opening day of his confirmation hearings verged on pandemonium. Dozens of screaming protesters were hauled out of the hearing room in handcuffs.

headline.main: Kavanaugh Portrayed as a Hopeless Partisan as Hearings on Supreme Court Nominee Open
headline.print_headline: Democrats Hurl Fierce Barrage At Court Choice
